function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> isuppercase(w[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` higher-order function to create a new array containing only the words that start with an uppercase letter. The anonymous function `w -> isuppercase(w[1])` returns `true` if the first character of the word `w` is uppercase, and `false` otherwise. `filter` then includes only the elements of `words` for which this anonymous function returns `true`.
